{"title":"Hat","url":"https://nethackwiki.com/wiki/Hat","type":"markdown","data":"In *[NetHack](/wiki/NetHack \"NetHack\")*, the term **hat** is used refer to any of the following [helms](/wiki/Helm \"Helm\") in certain messages:[\\[1\\]](#cite_note-1)\n\n- [cornuthaum](/wiki/Cornuthaum \"Cornuthaum\")\n- [dunce cap](/wiki/Dunce_cap \"Dunce cap\")\n- [elven leather helm](/wiki/Elven_leather_helm \"Elven leather helm\"), known as a \"leather hat\" when unidentified, or simply as a \"hat\" in variants that implement an [object materials](/wiki/Object_materials \"Object materials\") system\n- [fedora](/wiki/Fedora \"Fedora\")\n\nAdditionally, the [dwarvish iron helm](/wiki/Dwarvish_iron_helm \"Dwarvish iron helm\") appears as a *hard hat* when unidentified, but otherwise is always referred to as a *helm*.\n\nHats are generally non-rigid helms: they do not protect against falling objects, but can be worn while [polyselfed](/wiki/Polyself \"Polyself\") into a form with a horned [head](/wiki/Head \"Head\"), and wearing one lowers the amount of damage taken if you hit the ceiling from [quaffing](/wiki/Quaff \"Quaff\") a cursed [potion of levitation](/wiki/Potion_of_levitation \"Potion of levitation\").\n\n## References\n\n1. [↑](#cite_ref-1) [src/objnam.c in NetHack 3.6.7, line 4214](https://github.com/NetHack/NetHack/blob/NetHack-3.6.7_Released/src/objnam.c#L4214): *`helm_simple_name` function*\n\n[![This article has been updated to reflect NetHack 3.6.7. Click here for more information.](/images/f/f7/Nh367-icon.png)](/wiki/NetHackWiki:Next_version \"This article has been updated to reflect NetHack 3.6.7. Click here for more information.\")\n\n***\n\n*This is a [disambiguation](/wiki/NetHackWiki:Disambiguation \"NetHackWiki:Disambiguation\") page: a list of articles associated with the same title.*  \n*If an [internal link](https://nethackwiki.com/wiki/Special:WhatLinksHere/Hat) led you here, you may wish to change the link to point directly to the intended page.*\n","htm